Document: Binary Serialization API
Path: godot/tutorials/io/binary_serialization_api.rst
Summary: Describes how integers are encoded in the binary serialization API based on flags.

int
If no flags are set (flags == 0), the integer is sent as a 32 bit integer:
* Offset: 4
* Len: 4
* Type: Integer
* Description: 32-bit signed integer

If flag ENCODE_FLAG_64 is set (flags & 1 == 1), the integer is sent as a 64-bit integer:
* Offset: 4
* Len: 8
* Type: Integer
* Description: 64-bit signed integer
---CHUNK---
Document: binary_serialization_api
Path: godot/tutorials/io/binary_serialization_api.rst
Summary: Describes how float values are encoded in the binary serialization API based on flags.

float
If no flags are set (flags == 0), the float is sent as a 32-bit single-precision IEEE 754 float, occupying 4 bytes at offset 4.
If flag ENCODE_FLAG_64 is set (flags & 1 == 1), the float is sent as a 64-bit double-precision IEEE 754 float, occupying 8 bytes at offset 4.
---CHUNK---
Document: Binary Serialization API
Path: godot/tutorials/io/binary_serialization_api.rst
Summary: This section describes the binary serialization format for the String type.

The String type is serialized with the following structure:
*   String length (Integer): The length of the string in bytes. This field is located at offset 4 and has a length of 4 bytes.
*   UTF-8 encoded string (Bytes): The actual UTF-8 encoded string data. This field is located at offset 8 and has a variable length (X).
This field is padded to 4 bytes.
---CHUNK---
