Document: binary_serialization_api
Path: godot/tutorials/io/binary_serialization_api.rst
Summary: This section describes the binary serialization format for Transform2D.

Transform2D
- The X component of the X column vector, accessed via [0][0] (Float): Offset: 4, Length: 4.
- The Y component of the X column vector, accessed via [0][1] (Float): Offset: 8, Length: 4.
- The X component of the Y column vector, accessed via [1][0] (Float): Offset: 12, Length: 4.
- The Y component of the Y column vector, accessed via [1][1] (Float): Offset: 16, Length: 4.
- The X component of the origin vector, accessed via [2][0] (Float): Offset: 20, Length: 4.
- The Y component of the origin vector, accessed via [2][1] (Float): Offset: 24, Length: 4.
---CHUNK---
