Path: godot/tutorials/io/binary_serialization_api.rst
Summary: Describes the binary serialization format for the Basis type.
Basis
- X component of X column vector (Float): accessed via [0][0].
- Y component of X column vector (Float): accessed via [0][1].
- Z component of X column vector (Float): accessed via [0][2].
- X component of Y column vector (Float): accessed via [1][0].
- Y component of Y column vector (Float): accessed via [1][1].
- Z component of Y column vector (Float): accessed via [1][2].
- X component of Z column vector (Float): accessed via [2][0].
- Y component of Z column vector (Float): accessed via [2][1].
- Z component of Z column vector (Float): accessed via [2][2].
