Document: Transform3D
Path: godot/tutorials/io/binary_serialization_api.rst
Summary: This section details the binary serialization structure of a Transform3D object, including component offsets, lengths, and types.

Transform3D
*   Offset 4, Length 4, Type Float: The X component of the X column vector, accessed via [0][0]
*   Offset 8, Length 4, Type Float: The Y component of the X column vector, accessed via [0][1]
*   Offset 12, Length 4, Type Float: The Z component of the X column vector, accessed via [0][2]
*   Offset 16, Length 4, Type Float: The X component of the Y column vector, accessed via [1][0]
*   Offset 20, Length 4, Type Float: The Y component of the Y column vector, accessed via [1][1]
*   Offset 24, Length 4, Type Float: The Z component of the Y column vector, accessed via [1][2]
*   Offset 28, Length 4, Type Float: The X component of the Z column vector, accessed via [2][0]
*   Offset 32, Length 4, Type Float: The Y component of the Z column vector, accessed via [2][1]
*   Offset 36, Length 4, Type Float: The Z component of the Z column vector, accessed via [2][2]
*   Offset 40, Length 4, Type Float: The X component of the origin vector, accessed via [3][0]
*   Offset 44, Length 4, Type Float: The Y component of the origin vector, accessed via [3][1]
*   Offset 48, Length 4, Type Float: The Z component of the origin vector, accessed via [3][2]
---CHUNK---
